                    <floruit>He was a 7th-century East Syriac Christian saint and monk, who founded several monasteries in Mesopotamia and Persia.</floruit>
                    <birth when="0660">According to the hagiographical Syriac Life of John of Dailam, John was born in Ḥdattā, a town on the confluence of the Upper Zab and the Tigris, in AD 660</birth>
                    <death when="0738">He died in his monastery near Kashkar on 26 January 738 AD and is commemorated on <date type="diesNatalis" ref="ethiocal:Teqemt19">19 Ṭǝqǝmt</date> and <date type="diesNatalis" ref="ethiocal:Teqemt9">9 Ṭǝqǝmt</date></death>
